{{$NEXT}}

0.1.1  2026-03-22
  - Added mandatory `type` parameter to enqueue, dequeue, enqueue-many,
    dequeue-many, size, in-flight, failed, total, and stats — every queue
    instance now supports multiple job types on a single collection
  - listen gains :type named parameter (replaces hard-coded default)
  - Updated both test suites (01-basic, 02-battle) to pass type argument
  - Indexes updated to include `type` field in both compound index keys

0.1.0  2026-03-21
  - Initial release
  - enqueue / dequeue / ack / nack / fail — core job lifecycle
  - Priority scheduling (higher value dequeued first)
  - Delayed delivery via :delay(N) seconds
  - Configurable max-attempts per job or queue-wide default
  - reclaim-stale — re-queue processing jobs from crashed workers
  - purge / clear / drop — maintenance helpers
  - ensure-indexes — compound indexes for efficient dequeue and stale scan
  - size / in-flight / failed / total / stats — queue metrics
  - enqueue-many / dequeue-many / ack-many — bulk operations
  - listen — built-in blocking event loop with auto ack/nack
  - MongoDB::Queue.connect — convenience factory constructor
  - Human-readable _dt DateTime companions for all epoch fields
